Dr '''Janina Ramirez''' (born 1973) is a British historian. lecturer and TV presenter.<ref>Judith Woods [http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/8445957/Dr-Lucy-Worsley-Im-just-an-historian-who-wandered-into-TV.html "Dr Lucy Worsley: 'I<U+2019>m just an historian who wandered into TV'",] ''Daily Telegraph'' 13 April 2011</ref>

Dr Janina Ramirez gained a degree in English literature (specializing in Old and Middle English) from [[St Anne's College, Oxford]], before completed a post-graduate studies at the Centre for Medieval Studies, York.  She completed a art/literature PhD on the symbolism of birds, which led to a lectureship in York<U+2019>s Art History department, followed by lecturing posts at Winchester, Warwick, and Oxford.

== Television career ==
* ''Illuminations: The Private Lives of Medieval Kings'' 3-part series for [[BBC Four]], January 2012 

